1
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:43,760
I want to go for a walk.

2
00:02:16,319 --> 00:02:17,000
That day,

3
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,039
right over there,

4
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:20,960
Feng told me

5
00:02:21,919 --> 00:02:22,560
I'd been diagnosed.

6
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:26,159
Medicine today

7
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:28,240
has come a long way

8
00:02:29,039 --> 00:02:30,080
since back then.

9
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,520
Don't give up hope.

10
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:34,479
Feng comforted me,

11
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,120
saying, "Don't give up hope."

12
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:38,039
For the past two years,

13
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,240
that's what I've tried to do.

14
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:56,800
Six months ago,

15
00:02:57,599 --> 00:02:58,240
right here,

16
00:02:59,919 --> 00:03:00,919
I ran into

17
00:03:01,159 --> 00:03:02,199
a girl from our foreign languages department.

18
00:03:04,199 --> 00:03:05,319
But I was too scared to talk to her.

19
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:07,840
It was Xiaoran

20
00:03:07,879 --> 00:03:08,960
who got her WeChat for me.

21
00:03:11,479 --> 00:03:12,599
We talked for two weeks.

22
00:03:13,879 --> 00:03:15,120
We really clicked.

23
00:03:16,919 --> 00:03:17,560
Then

24
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,520
she started dating

25
00:03:20,879 --> 00:03:21,840
a guy majoring in Latin

26
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:22,400
at our school.

27
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:25,759
See?

28
00:03:26,319 --> 00:03:27,800
Learning a foreign language matters.

29
00:03:53,719 --> 00:03:55,159
Last time I had an acute episode

30
00:03:55,759 --> 00:03:56,439
and was brought here,

31
00:03:59,199 --> 00:04:00,400
your voice was trembling.

32
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:03,800
You just stood here,

33
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:05,560
completely frozen,

34
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,120
right over there.

35
00:04:15,199 --> 00:04:16,759
That was the first time I met Lu Dadong.

36
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:21,480
Who brought him in?

37
00:04:41,399 --> 00:04:43,000
I've walked through

38
00:04:44,279 --> 00:04:45,079
every corner of this hospital.

39
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,120
I know it better than my school.

40
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,160
It was right here

41
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,079
that I smoked

42
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:56,879
my first cigarette.

43
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,000
When did you ever smoke?

44
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:16,800
Dadong taught me.

45
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,680
I never imagined

46
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:34,439
Dadong and I

47
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:36,959
would be competing for the same heart.

48
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,399
Xiaorui,

49
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,079
actually,

50
00:05:45,879 --> 00:05:46,360
I really...

51
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,519
I understand, Yi.

52
00:05:52,199 --> 00:05:53,120
I believe my dad

53
00:05:55,439 --> 00:05:56,800
would understand your decision too.

54
00:06:01,879 --> 00:06:02,839
Ever since I was diagnosed,

55
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:04,759
you,

56
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:06,519
Xiaoran,

57
00:06:07,399 --> 00:06:07,920
and Feng

58
00:06:09,079 --> 00:06:10,160
have always stayed by my side.

59
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,480
Because you're doctors,

60
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,720
I've already had an unfair advantage.

61
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:18,519
So

62
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,399
how could I blame

63
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,920
the white coat you wear?

64
00:06:42,079 --> 00:06:42,959
Give me one too.

65
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:57,720
Light it.

66
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,199
Cup your hands around it.

67
00:07:02,399 --> 00:07:03,360
Inhale. Inhale.

68
00:07:17,879 --> 00:07:18,759
Xiaorui's all grown up.

69
00:07:22,879 --> 00:07:23,560
No kidding.

70
00:07:24,839 --> 00:07:25,759
I'm already twenty.

71
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,000
Sometimes,

72
00:07:30,959 --> 00:07:32,399
I wish you all

73
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,560
wouldn't focus on me so much.

74
00:07:36,399 --> 00:07:37,600
I don't want to be

75
00:07:37,639 --> 00:07:39,279
the focus

76
00:07:39,439 --> 00:07:40,040
and center of your lives.

77
00:07:41,079 --> 00:07:42,279
I'd actually feel more at ease.

78
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,360
And I hope you

79
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,160
can have it easier too.

80
00:07:53,319 --> 00:07:54,480
Twenty...

81
00:07:57,879 --> 00:07:59,279
What was I doing at twenty?

82
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,639
Your dad watched me every day,

83
00:08:05,439 --> 00:08:06,680
wouldn't let me get caught in the rain

84
00:08:07,759 --> 00:08:09,279
or play sports.

85
00:08:10,959 --> 00:08:12,279
I spent every day at school

86
00:08:12,959 --> 00:08:13,759
studying cases,

87
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,639
living in the library,

88
00:08:16,439 --> 00:08:17,319
and doing experiments.

89
00:08:20,319 --> 00:08:21,240
Don't worry, Xiaorui.

90
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:23,560
I promise

91
00:08:24,519 --> 00:08:25,360
your twenties

92
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:28,279
will be much easier than mine,

93
00:08:29,439 --> 00:08:30,000
and much happier.

94
00:08:35,399 --> 00:08:35,879
They will.

95
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:42,519
Yi,

96
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,399
how long did we wait

97
00:08:45,879 --> 00:08:46,960
for this donor?

98
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:48,840
Just over two months.

99
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,200
Less than three.

100
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,120
So waiting for a donor

101
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,440
isn't completely endless.

102
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:57,840
Exactly.

103
00:08:58,559 --> 00:08:59,399
Maybe in three months,

104
00:08:59,879 --> 00:09:00,440
six months,

105
00:09:00,919 --> 00:09:01,720
or by next spring,

106
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,519
you'll be a whole new person.

107
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,480
But before then,

108
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,879
you'll have to let me modify you.

109
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,799
I'm going to put a reactor

110
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:17,799
inside your body.

111
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:19,360
What do you think?

112
00:09:22,279 --> 00:09:23,159
A reactor?

113
00:09:23,879 --> 00:09:24,759
A cardiac resynchronization pacemaker

114
00:09:26,759 --> 00:09:27,559
with a defibrillator.

115
00:09:27,559 --> 00:09:28,440
The kind that suddenly

116
00:09:30,799 --> 00:09:31,159
shocks me?

117
00:09:33,399 --> 00:09:34,279
Right.

118
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,759
Once it's implanted,

119
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:41,360
you'll be much safer.

120
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:42,279
Then we can

121
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:43,480
wait with peace of mind

122
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,440
for the next donor.

123
00:09:54,159 --> 00:09:54,600
Are you willing?

124
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,159
Sure.

125
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:05,399
Then I'll be

126
00:10:09,559 --> 00:10:10,440
Iron Man with a reactor in my chest.

127
00:10:12,279 --> 00:10:13,039
Don't get ahead of yourself.

128
00:10:13,399 --> 00:10:14,240
At best,

129
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:16,679
you'll be an iron boy.

130
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:20,639
I'm twenty already.

131
00:10:21,799 --> 00:10:22,799
I can be Iron Man.

132
00:10:26,639 --> 00:10:28,399
The patient is a 30-year-old

133
00:10:28,519 --> 00:10:29,840
with end-stage heart failure,

134
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,639
NYHA Class IV.

135
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:32,720
He has survived

136
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:33,600
ECMO support,

137
00:10:33,919 --> 00:10:34,840
catheter-based thrombus fragmentation

138
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,000
for pulmonary embolism,

139
00:10:36,559 --> 00:10:38,080
and multiple brushes with death.

140
00:10:38,879 --> 00:10:40,120
Against this complex background,

141
00:10:40,399 --> 00:10:41,159
our transplant team

142
00:10:41,559 --> 00:10:43,559
rose to the challenge

143
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:45,759
and won this battle for a new heart.

144
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:48,039
I'd especially like to mention

145
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,320
the young lead surgeon

146
00:10:49,759 --> 00:10:50,919
on this operation,

147
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,720
Director Lin Yi.

148
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:55,799
After coming off bypass,

149
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,480
the donor heart developed right heart failure.

150
00:10:59,039 --> 00:11:00,879
Director Lin remained calm

151
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,080
and pulled the patient back from death,

152
00:11:02,519 --> 00:11:04,720
successfully saving a family.

153
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:33,039
Head Nurse Shen,

154
00:11:33,399 --> 00:11:34,200
please sit down for a while.

155
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,600
Standing nonstop will wear you out.

156
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:36,559
No, no.

157
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,440
With heart transplant patients,

158
00:11:38,559 --> 00:11:39,759
we can't let our guard down for a second.

159
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:40,559
Only by standing

160
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:41,840
can we stay fully alert.

161
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:42,879
Lately,

162
00:11:43,039 --> 00:11:43,960
I've required

163
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:44,960
all the nurses to do the same.

164
00:11:45,639 --> 00:11:46,559
It's an exceptional period.

165
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,759
Everyone has to work a little harder.

166
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,720
I can't be the first to break my own rule.

167
00:11:59,000 --> 00:11:59,759
I know

168
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:01,639
the nurses resent me.

169
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,039
They think I'm too strict,

170
00:12:03,159 --> 00:12:03,960
cold,

171
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:05,399
and work them like animals.

172
00:12:05,919 --> 00:12:06,559
But it can't be helped.

173
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:07,639
This is the job.

174
00:12:08,039 --> 00:12:09,440
This is how I, Shen Yaqin, work.

175
00:12:11,399 --> 00:12:12,879
Miss one detail,

176
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,720
and the patient could die.

177
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:16,440
You're right.

178
00:12:16,919 --> 00:12:17,960
I've always felt

179
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:19,639
that in the ICU,

180
00:12:19,639 --> 00:12:20,200
doctors and nurses

181
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:22,159
shouldn't only see the illness,

182
00:12:22,799 --> 00:12:23,399
but also

183
00:12:23,399 --> 00:12:24,679
the individual person.

184
00:12:27,039 --> 00:12:28,399
I think you're

185
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,240
especially perceptive

186
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:31,879
and very grounded.

187
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:36,440
Family upbringing really matters.

188
00:12:37,039 --> 00:12:38,519
With a role model like your mother,

189
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,320
your family

190
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,720
produced three doctors.

191
00:12:42,279 --> 00:12:43,320
Actually,

192
00:12:43,799 --> 00:12:45,320
my brother's situation

193
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,240
was different from mine.

194
00:12:46,519 --> 00:12:48,159
When he was very young,

195
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,039
Mom wasn't

196
00:12:49,039 --> 00:12:50,039
there for him.

197
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:52,000
He made it all the way on his own.

198
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:53,159
It wasn't easy.

199
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:54,600
Really?

200
00:12:55,759 --> 00:12:58,559
They only began mending things

201
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,759
in the past two years.

202
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:01,879
My brother built his career

203
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,519
without benefiting from Mom at all.

204
00:13:03,879 --> 00:13:04,879
If anything,

205
00:13:04,919 --> 00:13:06,360
being Professor Fang's son

206
00:13:06,559 --> 00:13:07,879
brought him a lot of criticism.

207
00:13:14,639 --> 00:13:15,360
How is Dadong?

208
00:13:15,879 --> 00:13:16,879
His condition is stable for now.

209
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,200
Sorry, Head Nurse.

210
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:31,360
Do you have a moment?

211
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:32,840
Could I speak with you?

212
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:34,559
Go ahead.

213
00:13:34,879 --> 00:13:35,559
I'll keep watch here.

214
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:36,600
And Beibei

215
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:37,279
should be here soon.

216
00:13:37,559 --> 00:13:37,919
All right.

217
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:38,919
I'll be back shortly.

218
00:13:51,639 --> 00:13:52,120
Head Nurse,

219
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,799
I'm truly sorry

220
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:54,639
about the conflict between Dr. Ye and Xiaojing.

221
00:13:54,799 --> 00:13:55,480
I've already

222
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:56,519
given Dr. Ye a stern reprimand

223
00:13:56,879 --> 00:13:58,360
and told her to apologize to Xiaojing.

224
00:13:59,039 --> 00:14:01,120
But clearly, I don't think

225
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:02,320
she has sincerely

226
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:03,720
recognized what she did wrong.

227
00:14:05,759 --> 00:14:06,559
That's also

228
00:14:06,559 --> 00:14:07,519
my responsibility as her supervisor.

229
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,320
I don't blame you, Director Zhou.

230
00:14:10,399 --> 00:14:10,759
No, no.

231
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:11,759
You were right.

232
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:13,639
If you hadn't pointed it out,

233
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:15,080
I wouldn't have realized

234
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,080
how much extra work

235
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,120
our nursing team was taking on.

236
00:14:18,279 --> 00:14:19,519
What exactly do you want?

237
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:20,919
Director Zhou punished me.

238
00:14:20,919 --> 00:14:22,080
For the next few days,

239
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:23,759
I have to follow you.

240
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,279
Follow me for what?

241
00:14:25,519 --> 00:14:26,240
Whatever you do, I do.

242
00:14:26,919 --> 00:14:28,120
I'll assist you.

243
00:14:28,799 --> 00:14:30,480
Daily blood pressure charts,

244
00:14:30,679 --> 00:14:32,080
four glucose checks before and after meals—

245
00:14:32,919 --> 00:14:34,080
the nurses handle all of that.

246
00:14:34,519 --> 00:14:36,159
Even arterial blood gases,

247
00:14:36,519 --> 00:14:37,399
which doctors do in other departments,

248
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,799
are also done by nurses here.

249
00:14:44,399 --> 00:14:46,360
It seems Director Zhou

250
00:14:46,639 --> 00:14:47,639
really took the time

251
00:14:47,639 --> 00:14:49,039
to understand our work.

252
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,120
When I was a resident,

253
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:52,200
I was terrible

254
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:53,320
at drawing arterial blood gases too.

255
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:55,200
It was the nurses

256
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,600
who taught me step by step.

257
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,440
Dr. Bai also used to say

258
00:14:59,039 --> 00:15:00,720
that we must learn more from nurses.

259
00:15:05,559 --> 00:15:07,159
It's a shame young doctors today

260
00:15:07,279 --> 00:15:08,799
no longer have that awareness.

261
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:10,720
They treat us nurses

262
00:15:10,799 --> 00:15:11,919
like ward attendants.

263
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:13,000
I promise

264
00:15:13,799 --> 00:15:14,519
nothing like this

265
00:15:14,519 --> 00:15:15,440
will happen again.

266
00:15:16,159 --> 00:15:17,320
I'll make the young doctors

267
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,519
do their own jobs properly.

268
00:15:19,039 --> 00:15:19,759
At the same time,

269
00:15:20,279 --> 00:15:21,559
if you're still willing,

270
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:23,279
I hope you'll keep teaching them.

271
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:26,279
I've learned my lesson this time.

272
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:27,200
In the future,

273
00:15:27,679 --> 00:15:28,799
I'll do better.

274
00:15:31,879 --> 00:15:32,759
I can be

275
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:33,960
a little sharp-tongued

276
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:34,840
when I'm anxious.

277
00:15:35,279 --> 00:15:36,200
Please don't take it personally.

278
00:15:36,519 --> 00:15:37,279
You're my senior.

279
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:38,559
I still need your guidance.

280
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,320
As for Dr. Ye,

281
00:15:42,759 --> 00:15:44,080
she still has a lot to improve,

282
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,399
but I believe she can

283
00:15:45,399 --> 00:15:46,639
become a good doctor.

284
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:48,039
I hope

285
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:49,440
you'll give her a little more time.

286
00:15:50,679 --> 00:15:51,720
And thank you

287
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:53,399
for agreeing to let her learn from Xiaojing.

288
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:54,120
I'm sure

289
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,360
she'll gain a lot from it.

290
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:57,840
She's lucky

291
00:15:58,039 --> 00:15:59,320
to have a supervisor like you.

292
00:16:01,159 --> 00:16:01,639
Head Nurse,

293
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:02,840
the ER

294
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:04,279
needs us to send over a ventilator.

295
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:04,879
Okay.

296
00:16:05,639 --> 00:16:06,120
Take it slowly.

297
00:16:08,639 --> 00:16:09,080
Let's go.

298
00:16:24,799 --> 00:16:26,200
I was already humiliated

299
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,159
for entering the wrong order that day.

300
00:16:27,799 --> 00:16:29,159
Then you exposed me in front of everyone.

301
00:16:30,039 --> 00:16:31,679
I felt completely embarrassed.

302
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:33,879
So that was my fault?

303
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:35,080
It was my fault.

304
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:40,480
I've followed you around for two days,

305
00:16:40,919 --> 00:16:42,519
and my legs can barely take it.

306
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:45,159
Your daily workload is so heavy,

307
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:46,000
yet you still noticed

308
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,000
my incorrect order.

309
00:16:48,039 --> 00:16:49,000
I'm impressed.

310
00:16:51,279 --> 00:16:52,600
And there's something else you're amazing at.

311
00:16:53,039 --> 00:16:54,480
No matter how thin or collapsed the vein is,

312
00:16:54,559 --> 00:16:55,960
you get it on the first try.

313
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,960
Even arterial blood gases—

314
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:00,000
one clean stick.

315
00:17:00,279 --> 00:17:01,480
That's basic technique, okay?

316
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:05,680
Do it enough and you get good at it.

317
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:06,839
But you're still so young.

318
00:17:07,119 --> 00:17:07,960
I'm not that young.

319
00:17:09,880 --> 00:17:11,240
I'm almost thirty.

320
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:14,680
Really? You don't look it at all.

321
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:19,759
Oh, spare me.

322
00:17:19,759 --> 00:17:20,799
I didn't mean

323
00:17:21,119 --> 00:17:22,079
to embarrass you.

324
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:23,400
I was just anxious.

325
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,480
Our head nurse says

326
00:17:24,559 --> 00:17:25,839
doctors and nurses

327
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,640
should back each other up.

328
00:17:27,759 --> 00:17:28,640
It's better to spend extra time

329
00:17:28,759 --> 00:17:29,839
double-checking

330
00:17:29,839 --> 00:17:30,640
than to slack off

331
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:32,559
and dump work on each other.

332
00:17:32,759 --> 00:17:33,640
Otherwise, mistakes happen easily,

333
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:35,400
and the patient pays the price.

334
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:39,839
Your head nurse is right.

335
00:17:47,039 --> 00:17:48,519
And so are you.

336
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,400
You're not still mad at me, are you?

337
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:52,640
Who does that?

338
00:17:52,839 --> 00:17:53,960
You tore into me in public,

339
00:18:00,839 --> 00:18:01,480
then apologized in private.

340
00:18:01,839 --> 00:18:03,440
And who drinks milk tea

341
00:18:06,039 --> 00:18:06,359
late at night?

342
00:18:07,119 --> 00:18:08,559
Go.

343
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:11,559
Make me a cup of lemon water.

344
00:18:29,039 --> 00:18:29,559
Still awake?

345
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:30,519
You're off work?

346
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,279
The head nurse gave me these.

347
00:18:32,359 --> 00:18:33,519
Winter jujubes from her hometown.

348
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:34,960
I brought some for you to try.

349
00:18:37,799 --> 00:18:38,200
Yi,

350
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:40,279
I want a few.

351
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:41,160
Wash some for me.

352
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:41,960
I'll do it.

353
00:18:42,559 --> 00:18:43,440
No need, Xiaoran.

354
00:18:44,079 --> 00:18:44,880
Let Yi go.

355
00:18:45,359 --> 00:18:46,200
He's been sitting there forever.

356
00:18:46,839 --> 00:18:47,759
It's fine. I'll go.

357
00:18:54,279 --> 00:18:55,200
How do you feel?

358
00:18:55,599 --> 00:18:56,200
Much better.

359
00:18:59,279 --> 00:19:00,039
How is Dongzi?

360
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,559
He's doing well.

361
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:05,880
You don't need to worry about him.

362
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:14,920
Sorry, Xiaoran.

363
00:19:17,119 --> 00:19:18,240
I lost control yesterday

364
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:21,000
and broke the cup

365
00:19:21,039 --> 00:19:21,759
you gave me.

366
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:23,720
It's okay.

367
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:25,400
We'll pick another design

368
00:19:25,599 --> 00:19:26,480
and make you a new one.

369
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:32,880
The jujubes are washed.

370
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:34,319
Eat them now.

371
00:19:35,759 --> 00:19:37,279
You washed too few.

372
00:19:37,519 --> 00:19:39,079
Go wash more. I want some too.

373
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:42,240
Why eat so many this late?

374
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:44,799
Fine, I'll wash them all.

375
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:57,680
Of all the plans you discussed,

376
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:58,920
I like

377
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:00,599
the Sunny Coast theme best.

378
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:03,759
You're proposing to Xiaoran?

379
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:05,079
When did you decide that?

380
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:07,599
You old iron tree

381
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:08,599
has finally bloomed.

382
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:09,759
Wait, has Xiaoran gone far enough?

383
00:20:10,279 --> 00:20:11,079
What are you doing?

384
00:20:11,119 --> 00:20:11,839
Don't get so excited.

385
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:12,519
What?

386
00:20:14,519 --> 00:20:15,039
For now,

387
00:20:17,079 --> 00:20:19,599
it's only a preliminary idea.

388
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:21,319
I still don't know

389
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:23,160
what to do next.

390
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,640
Do you want my help?

391
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:26,400
Have the parents formally propose?

392
00:20:26,839 --> 00:20:27,519
Prepare the betrothal gift?

393
00:20:28,039 --> 00:20:29,039
I have money, Yi.

394
00:20:29,039 --> 00:20:30,000
What nonsense is that?

395
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,839
That's all too conventional.

396
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,079
Conventional?

397
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:36,960
I...

398
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,440
want to give Xiaoran

399
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:44,599
the most unforgettable sense of ceremony

400
00:20:46,359 --> 00:20:47,200
in her life.

401
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:49,680
A sense of ceremony?

402
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:50,799
I know Xiaoran inside out.

403
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:51,559
Leave this to me.

404
00:20:52,799 --> 00:20:53,880
I'll handle it for you.

405
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:56,680
You already know?

406
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:57,200
Yi told you?

407
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:00,400
No.

408
00:21:00,519 --> 00:21:02,279
I think everyone could do

409
00:21:02,359 --> 00:21:03,559
a beach-resort theme.

410
00:21:04,559 --> 00:21:05,680
Look at Yi and my brother.

411
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:06,680
They're always in white coats

412
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:07,480
or scrubs.

413
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,279
It'd be hilarious

414
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:10,400
to see them in floral shirts.

415
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,759
But I disagree on one thing.

416
00:21:18,599 --> 00:21:20,519
Why hire an emcee?

417
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:22,000
That's expensive.

418
00:21:22,039 --> 00:21:23,519
Why waste money

419
00:21:23,759 --> 00:21:24,920
when we have free labor right here?

420
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:26,519
You'll be

421
00:21:26,799 --> 00:21:28,319
our designated emcee.

422
00:21:33,640 --> 00:21:34,200
Fine.

423
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:37,640
Then I'd better

424
00:21:38,519 --> 00:21:39,400
start practicing.

425
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:40,680
It's settled.

426
00:21:51,599 --> 00:21:53,119
Try one. They're really sweet.

427
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:58,839
Well? Sweet?

428
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:00,880
Way too sweet.

429
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,279
The cath lab?

430
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:08,960
Yes.

431
00:22:09,839 --> 00:22:11,000
I've wanted to ask you for a while.

432
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:13,119
Why can Du Wenzheng scrub in,

433
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,519
while I can only manage beds

434
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:15,720
and can't enter the cath lab?

435
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:19,440
It's a Cardiology tradition.

436
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:20,599
The radiation in the cath lab

437
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,039
does carry some risk,

438
00:22:22,160 --> 00:22:22,759
so women

439
00:22:22,759 --> 00:22:23,720
are given extra consideration.

440
00:22:24,119 --> 00:22:25,680
The usual practice is to wait until after childbirth.

441
00:22:28,279 --> 00:22:29,079
Then if

442
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:31,039
I never have children,

443
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:32,440
does that mean

444
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:33,319
I can never scrub in?

445
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:35,160
Of course not.

446
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,839
It depends on your own plans.

447
00:22:37,359 --> 00:22:38,519
I don't have plans like that.

448
00:22:39,119 --> 00:22:40,079
I don't want to date,

449
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:41,319
let alone marry and have children.

450
00:22:41,319 --> 00:22:42,480
But the window

451
00:22:42,839 --> 00:22:43,960
for learning technical skills

452
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:44,559
is precious.

453
00:22:44,759 --> 00:22:45,839
Fall behind once,

454
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:47,039
and you may keep falling behind.

455
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:49,400
Have you really thought it through?

456
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:50,720
Radiation exposure

457
00:22:50,759 --> 00:22:51,680
can't be ignored.

458
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:52,640
For me,

459
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:53,920
having children isn't essential.

460
00:22:54,119 --> 00:22:54,920
My career is.

461
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:56,680
Proper protection is enough.

462
00:22:57,359 --> 00:22:57,880
Besides,

463
00:22:58,240 --> 00:22:59,240
this unequal treatment

464
00:22:59,279 --> 00:23:00,680
in the name of protection is unfair.

465
00:23:01,359 --> 00:23:01,799
At least give me

466
00:23:01,799 --> 00:23:03,000
the right to choose.

467
00:23:06,319 --> 00:23:06,880
All right.

468
00:23:07,559 --> 00:23:08,039
Really?

469
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:09,640
Can I scrub in with you?

470
00:23:10,039 --> 00:23:10,440
Of course.

471
00:23:10,599 --> 00:23:11,720
You're already on my team.

472
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:13,200
I want to start as soon as possible.

473
00:23:13,480 --> 00:23:14,400
Today or tomorrow would be fine.

474
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:16,279
I'll have Zhang Zhen arrange it.

475
00:23:17,359 --> 00:23:18,160
Thank you, Dr. Zhou.

476
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:20,519
Thank you, Director.

477
00:23:21,119 --> 00:23:22,000
Call me whatever you like.

478
00:23:23,799 --> 00:23:25,039
See? You do know how to smile.

479
00:23:26,519 --> 00:23:27,680
Have you made up with Xiaojing?

480
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:30,880
She's all right.

481
00:23:32,319 --> 00:23:33,720
The cath lab! The cath lab!

482
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:35,279
I'll go get ready.

483
00:23:37,799 --> 00:23:39,000
Don't give your colleagues or patients

484
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:39,680
any more reason to complain about you.

485
00:23:39,799 --> 00:23:40,480
Got it.

486
00:24:03,079 --> 00:24:03,720
Director.

487
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:07,400
Director.

488
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:15,039
How is Xiaorui?

489
00:24:20,559 --> 00:24:21,599
He's relatively stable.

490
00:24:23,279 --> 00:24:24,319
Given his condition,

491
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:26,279
an LVAD would be an option,

492
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:30,079
but he's strongly opposed to it.

493
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:33,160
So

494
00:24:33,799 --> 00:24:34,839
the next step is

495
00:24:35,519 --> 00:24:36,559
to implant

496
00:24:36,559 --> 00:24:37,359
a CRT-D first,

497
00:24:37,519 --> 00:24:38,920
then keep waiting for a donor.

498
00:24:40,440 --> 00:24:40,839
Director,

499
00:24:41,799 --> 00:24:44,279
I'm very grateful for what you did for Xiaorui.

500
00:24:46,039 --> 00:24:46,519
But...

501
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:47,680
It's all right.

502
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:48,720
Look ahead.

503
00:24:50,960 --> 00:24:51,759
Do you still have surgery later?

504
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:54,000
I don't have any more today.

505
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:56,200
But Zhou Xiaofeng

506
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:57,680
has a pacemaker procedure later

507
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:58,640
and needs me on standby.

508
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,240
Installing a pacemaker

509
00:25:00,319 --> 00:25:01,279
requires you on standby?

510
00:25:03,319 --> 00:25:04,279
Because the patient

511
00:25:04,319 --> 00:25:05,200
was admitted through our joint clinic.

512
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:06,000
And this time,

513
00:25:06,519 --> 00:25:07,519
they're implanting

514
00:25:07,559 --> 00:25:08,680
a leadless pacemaker.

515
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:09,880
He also had a previous infection,

516
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:11,319
so the case is unusual.

517
00:25:11,759 --> 00:25:13,039
Current leadless pacemakers

518
00:25:13,079 --> 00:25:14,240
are all single-chamber, right?

519
00:25:14,640 --> 00:25:15,920
They're not suitable for every patient.

520
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:17,519
Right.

521
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:19,079
So this time they're using

522
00:25:19,119 --> 00:25:20,279
a new product from MyAmpere

523
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:21,200
that can simulate dual-chamber pacing.

524
00:25:22,319 --> 00:25:23,559
Cardiology has done

525
00:25:23,599 --> 00:25:24,680
a lot of business with MyAmpere lately.

526
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:27,799
Yes.

527
00:25:28,359 --> 00:25:29,720
Their products have shown up a lot.

528
00:25:30,359 --> 00:25:31,279
Is it still that Manager Ouyang?

529
00:25:32,559 --> 00:25:33,000
Yes.

530
00:25:34,599 --> 00:25:35,799
Then keep a close eye on things.

531
00:25:36,799 --> 00:25:38,519
Don't let your brother make a mistake.

532
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:47,640
The patient is a 72-year-old man

533
00:25:48,039 --> 00:25:48,519
with atrial fibrillation

534
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:50,680
and high-grade AV block.

535
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:51,400
He had a pacemaker implanted

536
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:52,680
fifteen years ago

537
00:25:52,839 --> 00:25:54,319
and the generator replaced

538
00:25:54,640 --> 00:25:55,960
three years ago.

539
00:25:56,079 --> 00:25:58,039
The two old leads

540
00:25:59,119 --> 00:25:59,960
are still inside his body.

541
00:26:00,359 --> 00:26:02,200
Why?

542
00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:04,279
Because after more than ten years,

543
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:05,519
the leads have essentially

544
00:26:05,599 --> 00:26:06,240
grown into the myocardium

545
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,200
and surrounding tissue.

546
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:08,960
As you can see,

547
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:09,799
they've also adhered

548
00:26:10,640 --> 00:26:11,480
to the vessel walls along their course.

549
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:12,759
If we try

550
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,039
to remove the leads,

551
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:15,079
we could easily cause

552
00:26:15,359 --> 00:26:15,920
vascular rupture

553
00:26:16,519 --> 00:26:17,799
and massive bleeding.

554
00:26:17,839 --> 00:26:18,839
That's why many doctors

555
00:26:19,799 --> 00:26:21,000
don't dare attempt it casually.

556
00:26:21,039 --> 00:26:21,880
So this time,

557
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:23,160
the infected leads

558
00:26:23,359 --> 00:26:23,720
are causing recurrent high fever?

559
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:25,119
Correct.

560
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:27,039
Director Zhou

561
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:28,720
will first extract the old leads,

562
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:30,119
then attempt to implant

563
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:31,880
a leadless pacemaker.

564
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:46,920
Puncture needle.

565
00:26:47,799 --> 00:26:49,279
How do you locate

566
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,200
the femoral vein puncture site?

567
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:51,720
Two centimeters below

568
00:26:51,799 --> 00:26:52,480
the inguinal ligament,

569
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:53,680
on the line from

570
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:54,640
the anterior superior iliac spine

571
00:26:58,119 --> 00:26:59,440
to the pubic tubercle,

572
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:00,400
at the junction of the medial

573
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:02,359
and middle thirds,

574
00:27:03,839 --> 00:27:04,960
0.5 to 1 centimeter

575
00:27:05,359 --> 00:27:07,119
medial to the arterial pulse.

576
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,000
That young doctor

577
00:27:08,079 --> 00:27:08,799
doesn't look familiar.

578
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:13,559
She's a new specialty trainee, Ye.

579
00:27:13,759 --> 00:27:14,680
A trainee?

580
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:15,480
Her movements are efficient,

581
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:16,400
and she reacts quickly.

582
00:27:16,839 --> 00:27:18,160
She's sharp.

583
00:27:18,519 --> 00:27:19,240
You may not believe it,

584
00:27:22,279 --> 00:27:24,119
but this is her first time

585
00:27:24,119 --> 00:27:25,079
scrubbing in with the director.

586
00:27:25,279 --> 00:27:26,599
That tells you

587
00:27:26,920 --> 00:27:28,200
how hard she prepared in private.

588
00:27:28,359 --> 00:27:29,559
She's very diligent.

589
00:27:29,559 --> 00:27:30,480
Then your position

590
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:31,640
as first assistant

591
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:32,640
is in danger.

592
00:27:36,119 --> 00:27:36,559
Why aren't you worried?

593
00:28:28,599 --> 00:28:29,359
What do I have to worry about?

594
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:07,079
I wish we had

595
00:29:19,759 --> 00:29:20,119
ten more promising young doctors like her

596
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:21,599
to share

597
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:25,440
all the work I can't finish.

598
00:29:39,599 --> 00:29:40,240
C-arm.

599
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:41,559
Thirty degrees right anterior oblique.

600
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,200
Angiography.

601
00:29:46,359 --> 00:29:47,319
Beautiful.

602
00:29:47,559 --> 00:29:48,480
It crossed the valve smoothly.

603
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:49,640
Prepare to deploy.

604
00:30:03,240 --> 00:30:03,599
Deployment complete.

605
00:30:04,279 --> 00:30:04,799
Check the parameters.

606
00:30:09,759 --> 00:30:10,480
Sensing, 7.9.

607
00:30:39,480 --> 00:30:40,759
Impedance, 790.

608
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:43,799
Threshold, 0.5.

609
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:46,319
The parameters are good.

610
00:30:47,039 --> 00:30:48,599
Dr. Ye,

611
00:30:59,079 --> 00:31:00,240
come here.

612
00:31:00,920 --> 00:31:02,240
Feel it.

613
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:03,559
Remember this moment.

614
00:31:04,559 --> 00:31:05,359
Your hands

615
00:31:05,799 --> 00:31:06,599
can help countless hearts

616
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:08,000
beat strongly and normally again.

617
00:31:08,599 --> 00:31:09,559
This looks so familiar.

618
00:31:42,319 --> 00:31:42,880
The first procedure I scrubbed in on

619
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:44,400
was also a pacemaker implantation.

620
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:45,400
Director Zhou

621
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:46,160
also had me

622
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:46,880
feel the patient's heartbeat.

623
00:31:47,279 --> 00:31:48,119
I'll never forget it.

624
00:31:48,559 --> 00:31:49,160
Dr. Zhou,

625
00:31:50,039 --> 00:31:51,079
I've confirmed everything

626
00:31:51,119 --> 00:31:52,119
with the village.

627
00:31:52,599 --> 00:31:53,480
We just need to arrive

628
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:54,880
at eight Saturday morning.

629
00:31:55,839 --> 00:31:57,160
All right.

630
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,680
Where are you going?

631
00:31:58,720 --> 00:31:59,920
To provide a free clinic in the countryside.

632
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:02,440
You're already run off your feet.

633
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:03,880
